except in the mind's judgment. Growth is usually considered \
positive, but nothing can grow forever. If growth, of what- \
ever kind, were to go on and on, it would eventually become \
monstrous and destructive. Dissolution is needed for new \
growth to happen. One cannot exist without the other. \
