\
I know that the word choose is a favorite New Age term, but \
it isn't entirely accurate in this context. It is misleading to say \
that somebody "chose" a dysfunctional relationship or any \
other negative situation in his or her life. Choice implies \
consciousness \'97 a high degree of consciousness. Without it, \
you have no choice. Choice begins the moment you disiden- \
tify from the mind and its conditioned patterns, the moment \
you become present. Until you reach that point, you are un- \
conscious, spiritually speaking. This means that you are com- \
pelled to think, feel, and act in certain ways according to the \
conditioning of your mind. That is why Jesus said: "Forgive \
